<<<<<How to Run>>>>>

  ================================================================================
    QUICK START
  ================================================================================
    apptainer run --bind /my/code:/code container.sif jupyter

  (CPU-only — no --nv / --rocm needed.)


  ================================================================================
    MODES & FLAGS
  ================================================================================
    MODES (this container ships one built-in mode)
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
      jupyter (default)   JupyterLab
        apptainer run --bind /my/code:/code --bind /my/data:/data \
          container.sif jupyter

    FLAGS
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
      --bind src:dst     apptainer exec --bind /my/code:/code --bind /my/data:/data \
                          --bind /my/output:/output container.sif <cmd>

      --env KEY=VALUE    apptainer exec --env OMP_NUM_THREADS=4 \
                          --bind /my/code:/code container.sif python /code/train.py

    Directories to bind: /code /data /output /model /scratch


  ================================================================================
    RUN YOUR OWN SCRIPT (EXEC)
  ================================================================================
    apptainer exec \
      --bind /my/code:/code --bind /my/data:/data --bind /my/output:/output \
      container.sif python /code/train.py


  ================================================================================
    SLURM — SINGLE NODE
  ================================================================================
    #!/bin/bash
    #SBATCH --job-name=classical-ml-train
    #SBATCH --cpus-per-task=8
    #SBATCH --mem=32G
    #SBATCH --partition=cpu
    #SBATCH --output=./logs/logs_%j.out
    #SBATCH --error=./logs/logs_%j.err
    #SBATCH --time=02:00:00

    echo "===================================="
    echo "Job Name   : $SLURM_JOB_NAME"
    echo "CPUs       : $SLURM_CPUS_PER_TASK"
    echo "===================================="

    srun apptainer exec \
      --bind /my/code:/code --bind /my/data:/data --bind /my/output:/output \
      container.sif python /code/train.py

    echo "===================================="
    echo "Training Completed"
    echo "===================================="

    No multi-node section — this stack (xgboost/lightgbm/sklearn on tabular
    data) is single-process, single-node by design. Size --cpus-per-task to
    your core count and let the library parallelize internally.


  ================================================================================
    CHECKING IT WORKS
  ================================================================================
    apptainer test container.sif

